704970f-a.title: Brooklyn: Hopkins Street - Throop Avenue
704970f-a.text:
208-234 Hopkins Street, south side, between Throop and Sumner Aves.,
shoming a building (No. 224), once occupied by the Hopkins Street Presbyteriwn
Church, now the 1st Rumanian Synagogue.
June 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
